description: The HELIOSKRILL is a work of art crafted by a Sangheili prodigy inspired to test her skill against the best that humanity could muster.

name: Helioskrill Bloodgorger
description: The HELIOSKRILL is a work of art crafted by a Sangheili prodigy inspired to test her skill against the best that humanity could muster.

name: Helioskrill Warbound
description: The HELIOSKRILL is a work of art crafted by a Sangheili prodigy inspired to test her skill against the best that humanity could muster.

name: Helljumper
description: A small number of HELLJUMPER prototypes have entered Spartan service under a research partnership between the UNSC and Cascade Stronghold Technology.

name: Helljumper Feet First
description: A small number of HELLJUMPER prototypes have entered Spartan service under a research partnership between the UNSC and Cascade Stronghold Technology.

name: Hermes
description: The Enhanced Mobility Subsystem embedded in the HERMES prototype is so powerful that only a handful of Spartans can use it safely.

name: Hermes Dolios
description: The Enhanced Mobility Subsystem embedded in the HERMES prototype is so powerful that only a handful of Spartans can use it safely.

name: Hunter
description: Sophisticated and lethal, HUNTER-class armor incorporates Watershed Division's latest warfighting technology.

name: Locus
description: Designed to provide an answer to threats arising during assaults on heavily defended tactical nodes, the grim visage of LOCUS armor is a common sight among Spartan boarding parties and special response teams.

name: Locus Edge
description: Designed to provide an answer to threats arising during assaults on heavily defended tactical nodes, the grim visage of LOCUS armor is a common sight among Spartan boarding parties and special response teams.

name: Marauder Keres
description: A rarity in an age of highly-specialized Mjolnir variants, MARAUDER is a general-purpose powered assault armor that takes full advantage of line-replaceable modules and reprogrammable sensor arrays for maximum flexibility.

name: Mark IV GEN1
description: As the basis for the GEN1 Mjolnir standard, many components of the original Mark IV can be used with GEN2 techsuits and VISRs after firmware updates. This hybrid MARK IV GEN1 suit is still used by select Spartan-II's.

name: Mark IV GEN1 Arcadia
description: As the basis for the GEN1 Mjolnir standard, many components of the original Mark IV can be used with GEN2 techsuits and VISRs after firmware updates. This hybrid MARK IV GEN1 suit is still used by select Spartan-II's.

name: Mark V Alpha
description: The Mark V and its product-improved variant, the Mark V B, were the first Mjolnir armors to fully integrate shield emitters and sufficient computing power for an onboard Smart AI. The MARK V ALPHA is a highly configurable revamp of the original.

name: Mark V Alpha Reflex
description: The Mark V and its product-improved variant, the Mark V B, were the first Mjolnir armors to fully integrate shield emitters and sufficient computing power for an onboard Smart AI. The MARK V ALPHA is a highly configurable revamp of the original.

name: Mark VI GEN1
description: Technically obsolete, the Mark VI GEN1 Mjolnir armor maintains a legendary luster among Spartans and the general public.

name: Mark VI GEN1 Scarred
description: The rugged Mark VI is able to remain functional until all of its triply-redundant auto-repair and bypass nodes fail.

name: Mark VI Primus
description: Without question the most famous of all Mjolnir permutations, the GEN2 MARK VI has been completely updated to modern powered assault armor standards.

name: Mark VI Regent
description: Without question the most famous of all Mjolnir permutations, the GEN2 MARK VI has been completely updated to modern powered assault armor standards.

name: Maverick Jester
description: MAVERICK-class armor uses a modular power pack that can be swapped out for a compact fusion reactor, radiothermal generator, or energy cell.

name: Nightfall
description: Spartans with Marine experience prefer NIGHTFALL armor when stationed on inhospitable worlds, due to its best-of-class life support.

name: Noble Honor
description: Reborn from the ashes of the Covenant War, NOBLE-class armor integrates the best battle network management hardware with the latest GEN2 techsuit features and dissipative shields.

name: Orbital Equinox
description: Patrolling Spartans equipped with ORBITAL-class Mjolnir armor are a common sight near Earth's orbital tethers and military space stations.

name: Raider
description: RAIDER-class armor has become the unofficial standard for Spartans assigned to military police duties.

name: Reaper Mortician
description: Design features sourced from the remnants of Forerunner combat skins have been directly incorporated into REAPER-class armor, but their compatibility with human operators has yet to be fully assessed.

name: Scout Outrider
description: In addition to sensor shrouding, SCOUT armor incorporates AI-assisted forward observation uplinks to direct aerospace and orbital strikes.

name: Shinobi Heartless
description: Discovered aboard a derelict freighter in Lacaille 9352, SHINOBI armor has no known manufacturer or intended user. ONI continues to probe the recovered suits to unlock what appears to be several levels of restricted functionality.

name: Technician
description: The TECHNICIAN Mjolnir system features a battlenet node and custom machine interlink that can process and curate vast amounts of data.

name: Technician Override
description: The TECHNICIAN Mjolnir system features a battlenet node and custom machine interlink that can process and curate vast amounts of data.

name: Venator Cestus
description: Lethbridge Industrial has incorporated feedback from Requiem veterans to improve the VENATOR's power management subsystem and reduce its maintenance requirements.

name: Venator Thraex
description: Lethbridge Industrial has incorporated feedback from Requiem veterans to improve the VENATOR's power management subsystem and reduce its maintenance requirements.

name: Void Dancer
description: The VOID DANCER answers many tactical questions for the UNSC special forces community, but its unique design features have raised alarms in ONI.

name: Void Dancer Comet
description: The VOID DANCER answers many tactical questions for the UNSC special forces community, but its unique design features have raised alarms in ONI.

name: War Master Augustan
description: WAR MASTER-class armor is a de-facto standard among the elite Headhunters: Spartan-IV covert operatives tasked with sabotage, counterinsurgency operations, and strategic reconnaissance.

name: War Master Scipio
description: WAR MASTER-class armor is a de-facto standard among the elite Headhunters: Spartan-IV covert operatives tasked with sabotage, counterinsurgency operations, and strategic reconnaissance.
